@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home</PageTitle>

<h1>Welcome to the Fraction Input Prototype!</h1>

<div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
    <h4 class="alert-heading">Variable Fraction Entry System</h4>
    <p>
        This web application demonstrates a solution for entering variable fractions without 
        the limitations of a predefined dropdown list.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="row mt-4">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card mb-3">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">The Problem</h5>
                <p class="card-text">
                    Traditional dropdown lists become unwieldy when supporting many fractions 
                    (e.g., 1/30 through 29/30, plus all preceding fractions like 1/6, 1/7, etc.).
                    This results in hundreds of options that are difficult to navigate.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card mb-3">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">The Solution</h5>
                <p class="card-text">
                    Instead of a dropdown, users can directly enter any fraction using two 
                    simple input fields: one for the numerator and one for the denominator.
                    The system validates input and shows the simplified form.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="mt-4">
    <h3>Get Started</h3>
    <p>
        Try one of our fraction input methods:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="fraction-input" class="btn btn-sm btn-primary">Fraction Input</a> - Enter numerator and denominator separately</li>
        <li><a href="fraction-regex" class="btn btn-sm btn-primary">Fraction Regex</a> - Enter fraction as "numerator/denominator" with regex validation</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="mt-4">
    <h4>Key Features:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>✓ Enter any fraction (e.g., 1/30, 15/30, 29/30)</li>
        <li>✓ Multiple input methods (separate fields or single regex-validated field)</li>
        <li>✓ Real-time validation</li>
        <li>✓ Automatic simplification to lowest terms</li>
        <li>✓ Display decimal and percentage equivalents</li>
        <li>✓ Clean, intuitive interface</li>
        <li>✓ No dropdown limitations</li>
    </ul>
</div>
